cli/output/tokenize.go exports tokenizeLine(line string) []Token where Token{Type string; Text string} and Type is one of: "comment", "string", "keyword", "number", "plain". The tokenizer is a single-pass character scanner with states for string tracking (double-quote, single-quote, backtick) and comment detection (//, #, -- at word boundaries). Comment markers require preceding whitespace, start-of-line, or semicolon to avoid false positives on URLs and operators. The keyword set is a package-level map of ~80 common cross-language words (if, else, for, return, func, def, class, import, const, nil, true, false, etc.). Number detection matches digit sequences optionally containing a single dot. The tokenizer is language-agnostic by design — no file extension lookup, no per-language grammar. See <ref spec="output.code_colorization">code colorization</ref> and <ref spec="principles.language_agnostic">language agnostic</ref>.